Senate President, Ahmed Lawan and Femi Fani-Kayode, a social commentator and chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, on Saturday reacted to the death of President Muhammadu Buhari’s Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari. DAILY POST reports that Kyari’s death was announced by Buhari’s Spokesman, Femi Adesina. He died after battling the deadly Coronavirus. Reacting, Lawan while praying for his soul, said ”death is inevitable.” He wrote on Twitter, “Death is inevitable, it only comes at our individually appointed time. “May Allah forgive the shortcomings of late Mallam Abba Kyari and grant him speedy passage to Aljannatu Firdausi.” Also, Fani-Kayode described Kyari as his, ‘friend of 40 years. He said, ”I have lost a friend of 40 years. We were at Cambridge together. We worked in my fathers law firm together. “We remained close throughout, right up until the end, even though we disagreed politically. Abba was a good man: a man of honour and a loyal friend. May his soul Rest In Peace.”